Carbide Industries Blast Kills Worker, Courier-Journal Says

-- B y   J a n e   L e e
-- 
2011-03-22T04:37:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/carbide-industries-blast-kills-worker-courier-journal-says.html
An explosion and fire at Carbide
Industries LLC’s chemical plant in Louisville,  Kentucky ,
yesterday killed a worker and injured three others, the  Courier-
Journal  reported on its website, citing Sal Melendez, a
spokesman for Louisville Fire and Rescue Department.  Carbide Industries is  North America ’s largest producer of
calcium carbide products, according to the  company’s website .
The material is used in iron foundries and steel plants.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jane Lee in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
